article.headline: DePaul 66, Houston 54
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Delonte Holland scored 19 points and Quemont Greer and Andre Brown added 16 apiece to lead DePaul to a 66-54 win over Houston Saturday night. Greer also grabbed 11 rebounds for DePaul (15-7, 8-3 Conference USA), which led 32-29 at halftime and put the game out of reach with a 9-0 run early in the second half. Houston (8-14, 2-9) got 11 points each from Lanny Smith and Andrew Owens. Anwar Ferguson added 10 points, 13 rebounds and three blocks. The lead changed 11 times in the first half, with Houston gaining a 21-17 lead with just under eight minutes left after a dunk by Ramon Dyer. DePaul quickly regained the lead by scoring five straight points to go up 22-21.
